    "The results of the proposed method were effective and deserving of consideration, and achieved the best prediction which was 0.59 within MAE and 0.785 within RMSE.",
    "Nabil et al (2021) identified students who were at risk of failure at an early stage of the semester based on their previous course's grades.",
    "The dataset included 4266 records that included demographic, academic, and behavioral features from a public university data set.",
    "Various resampling techniques, including SMOTE, ROS, ADASYN, and SMOTE-ENN, are used to address the imbalanced class, thereby enhancing model performance and producing accurate results.",
    "The results showed that the best result was obtained when training the predictive model using DNN and a balanced dataset using SMOTE as an oversampling method with an accuracy of up to 89%."
